cs.CR, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the implementation of security policies for digital objects, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of the Fedora architecture for digital objects and repositories suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and databases (cs.DB). The need for adapting to the evolution of digital objects and allowing them to move among repositories and portable devices suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of security automata suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL).
